{"lemma":"سَطْعٌ","slug":"سَطْعٌ","root":"س.ط.ع","root_slug":"س-ط-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ط-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19734","n19737"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to brighten"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to glare"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shine"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sa.tˤa.ʕa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19734","headword_ar":"سَطَعَ","root":"sTE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, * Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suTuwEN","text_ar":"سُطُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saToEN","text_ar":"سَطْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTiyEN","text_ar":"سَطِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last is rare, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It rose:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it spread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diffused itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA:) said of duct, and of the dawn, (S, Msb, K,) [meaning as above, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it radiated, gleamed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saATiEN","text_ar":"سَاطِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)] and of light, (TA,) and of lightning, and of the rays of the sun, (K,) and (tropical:)  of odour, (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) in relation to which last it is tropical, and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it diffused itself, and rose:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it was originally said only of light; and was then used absolutely, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it appeared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became apparent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTaEa Als~ahomu","text_ar":"سَطَعَ السَّهْمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The arrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"being shot,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose into the sky, glistening."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasoTaEu","text_ar":"يَسْطَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the aor. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTaEa","text_ar":"سَطَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is used by Dhu-r-Rummeh, in describing an ostrich, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He raises his head, and stretches his neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTaEa liY A^amoruka","text_ar":"سَطَعَ لِى اَمْرُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thine affair became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become, apparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manifest, to me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTaEatoniY raAy^iHapu Almisoki","text_ar":"سَطَعَتْنِى رَايِحَةُ المِسْكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The odour of the musk rose to my nose."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTaEotu Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"سَطَعْتُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I laid hold of the thing with the palm of the hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the hand, striking"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTaEa biyadayohi","text_ar":"سَطَعَ بِيَدَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saToEN","text_ar":"سَطْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clapped with his hands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the subst."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTaEN","text_ar":"سَطَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (IDrd, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTiEa","text_ar":"سَطِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saTaEN","text_ar":"سَطَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was long-necked; he had a long neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoTaEu","text_ar":"اَسْطَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Mgh","Msb","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n19737","headword_ar":"سَطَعٌ","root":"sTE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Length of neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) It is said of Mo- hammad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Eunuqihi saTaEN","text_ar":"فِى عُنُقِهِ سَطَعٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his neck was length."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoTaEu","text_ar":"اَسْطَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A clapping with the hands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"striking with one hand upon the other,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1359},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the hand of another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a striking a thing with the palm of the hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the fingers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound of a striking"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"throwing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEotu liwaqoEihi saTaEFA","text_ar":"سَمِعْتُ لِوَقْعِهِ سَطَعًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adiydFA","text_ar":"شَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I heard, in consequence of its falling, a loud sound of a striking"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"throwing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) It is with fet-h to the medial radical because it is an onomatopœia, not an epithet nor an inf. n., for onomatopœias are sometimes made to differ [in form] from epithets. (Lth, K.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}